<font color="#FF0000">PREGNANCY</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jul 23 17:46:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Many smart educated women who &quot;should know better&quot; get pregnant.  So this is not necessarily about whether or not girls like to use condoms or are knowledgeable about birth control.  A lot of times young girls are curious about their sexuality and the way their bodies work.  Since sex is a new thing for them, just as having their periods and puberty was very recently new to them, the fact that their behavior may lead to pregnancy may not be a reality until it hits home. A majority of my friends got pregnant in their teens and early twenties and it's not because they didn't know better or necessarily because of a lack of self esteem or contraception.  Most chose to have abortions and the few who didn't are the ones who had the least other options or aspirations in terms of career or education.  Perhaps this is the way De'Yona felt, in addition to being upset by her cousin's death.  If young women have options they tend not to want to be teenage mothers, but lots of all kinds of women have unwanted pregnancies.
